g.text: Zero Motorcycles BLE Worm Propagation - Attack Flowchart
1. Static firmware signing salt - attacker computes valid signatures
2. No MAC address filtering in MBB - accepts connections from any device
3. No application-layer authentication after BLE pairing
4. Unauthenticated firmware update protocol - only hash verification (attacker controlled)
5. Pairing mode accepts all connections - no user confirmation required on bike
* Protected bikes become vulnerable when put into pairing mode by user
